  <title class="- topic/title ">About Offers</title>
  <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc ">An offer is the content displayed
	 within an mbox during campaigns and tests. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Target" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Advanced" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
    <p class="- topic/p ">When you test your Web pages, you measure the success
		of each Web page configuration with different offers in your mboxes. 
	 </p>
    <p class="- topic/p ">For example, the following graphic shows a Web page
		with an mbox that could display either of two offers, depending on whether the
		visitor purchased a women's item or a men's item on a previous visit: 
	 </p>
    <p class="- topic/p ">
      <image id="image_3A7AE49287FF47EE82A9C7FBAAE4D883" href="graphics/offer_reduced.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image "></image>
    </p>
    <p class="- topic/p ">Offers are the content that displays within the mbox.
		An 
		<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i "><xref href="c_Experiences.xml#concept_B91F0F36E9F24AA58A3C6BC0A02871E8" type="concept" format="dita" scope="local" class="- topic/xref ">experience</xref></i> determines which offer displays
		when particular conditions are met. 
	 </p>
  </conbody>
